Mollie McConnell https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mollie_McConnell 0 Mollie McConnell (September 24, 1865 – December 9, 1920) was an American silent film actress. Before her 1913 movie debut, she was a national and international theater performer. In 1914, she signed a contract with Balboa Amusement Producing Company and played matronly roles in many of their films. She starred with William Garwood in the 1914 western A Ticket to Red Horse Gulch. Mollie_McConnell ( September_24_,_1865 – December_9_,_1920 ) was an_American_silent_film_actress .
